The paper deals with the problem of flip distance between two triangulations of a set of points in the plane, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The algorithm presented in the paper has a fixed-parameter tractable (FPT) running time, which suggests that it involves some form of parameterized complexity. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the NP-hardness of the problem, which indicates that it involves some form of computational complexity theory. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
